doc.ContractDescription: G:OTHER, RECHARGEABLE BATTERIES, RADIO BATTERY REPLACEMENTS FOR CUVA. MODIFICATION 1 REPLACES LINE 10 WITH LINE 20 DUE TO AN ADMINISTRATIVE ERROR. MODIFICATION 2 IS TO SECURE A 10% DISCOUNT DUE TO AN EXTREME DELIVERY DELAY. INITIALLY THE VENDOR HAD PRODUCTION DELAYS AND STATED ON AUGUST 3RD: "WE HAVE BEEN INFORMED BY PRODUCTION THAT THE BOARDS THAT WERE ORIGINALLY MANUFACTURED HAD A CHIP ISSUE ON THEM, THIS ISSUE WAS FOUND AFTER THE PACK WAS FINALLY PUT TOGETHER AND THE BATTERIES WERE BEING TESTED DURING FINAL Q&A CHECK. THE NEW BOARDS HAVE ARRIVED TODAY AND ARE BEING PUT INTO PRODUCTION FOR THESE BATTERIES TO SHIP OUT BY TUESDAY 8/9/16." NO WORD ON SHIPMENT WAS RECEIVED ON 8/9. THE CS INQUIRED SEVERAL TIMES VIA EMAIL AND DID NOT RECEIVE A REPLY. THE CS CALLED ON 8/17 AND WAS TOLD THAT THE ITEMS WOULD ARRIVE IN 2 BUSINESS DAYS; TRACKING NUMBERS WERE PROVIDED. ON 8/25, THE USPS ATTEMPTED TO DELIVER THE BOXES TO THE WRONG LOCATION (THE CONTRACTING OFFICE INSTEAD OF THE PARK). THE SHIPMENT WAS REJECTED DUE TO POSTAGE DUE. THE ITEMS ARE EN ROUTE BACK TO THE VENDOR WHERE THEY WILL BE REROUTED TO THE CORRECT ADDRESS.
